cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.PL, cs.DC

This paper deals with security vulnerabilities in Android browser apps, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves designing an automated system to test the vulnerability of browser apps, which could be considered as software engineering (cs.SE) and system integration (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the technical details of the attacks and the patches made by the developers, which could be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
